@startuml
title Viaverse Capability — Class Model

class Account {
  id: AccountId
  status: AccountStatus
  locale: Locale
  activeMode: AppMode?
  createdAt: Instant
}

class AccountCapability {
  accountId: AccountId
  type: CapabilityType
  status: CapabilityStatus
  reason: String?
  enabledAt: Instant?
  suspendedAt: Instant?
}

class BusinessProfile {
  id: BusinessId
  ownerAccountId: AccountId
  status: BusinessStatus
  verificationStatus: VerificationStatus
  publicSlug: String?
}

class BusinessTeamMember {
  businessId: BusinessId
  accountId: AccountId
  role: BusinessRole
  status: MemberStatus
}

enum AppMode {
  PERSONAL
  WORK
  BUSINESS
}

class CapabilityPolicy {
  canEnterMode()
  canEnableCapability()
  canSuspendCapability()
  requiresVerification()
}

class CapabilityAuditLog {
  id: UUID
  accountId: AccountId
  capabilityType: CapabilityType
  action: String
  reason: String?
  actorId: AccountId?
  createdAt: Instant
}

class CapabilityEvents {
  AccountCapabilityEnabled
  AccountCapabilitySuspended
  AccountCapabilityRevoked
  ActiveModeChanged
  BusinessProfileCreated
}

Account "1" o-- "*" AccountCapability
Account "1" o-- "*" BusinessProfile : owner
BusinessProfile "1" o-- "*" BusinessTeamMember
Account --> AppMode : activeMode
CapabilityPolicy ..> AccountCapability : checks
CapabilityPolicy ..> BusinessProfile : checks
AccountCapability --> CapabilityAuditLog : changes audited
CapabilityAuditLog ..> CapabilityEvents : emits

note bottom
Domain rule:
Capability is not a role label in UI only.
It is a persisted authorization input used by backend policies.
end note
@enduml
